channel.title: Velocity/Speed Question
channel.description:
Here it is, just tell me the answer please ;D
A ball is thrown straight up at an initial velocity if 53 feet per second. In the first 1.5 seconds it travels 42 feet. The formula s=(u+v/2)t represents the vertical distance S that an object travels in T seconds, when you represent the initial velocity of the object at the end of the T seconds. find the velocity of the ball.
Thanks in Advance
P.s. (u+v/2) is actually a fraction but I cant do it here.
